. Pricing plans\n6. Customer testimonials\n7. Call-to-action\n8. Footer with additional navigation and copyright\n\nNext steps would involve creating a corresponding CSS file to implement the clean purple and white design inspired by Linear and Notion, and adding actual content from the previously generated content.txt file.\n\n### css_styler\nI've completed the CSS design for the FlowSync landing page, carefully matching the HTML structure and implementing a clean, modern design inspired by Linear and Notion. \n\nKey Design Features:\n✅ Purple and white color scheme (#8A3FFC primary, #F8F9FC secondary)\n✅ Inter font stack with system font fallbacks\n✅ Responsive grid and flex layouts\n✅ Subtle shadows and hover effects\n✅ Mobile-friendly media queries\n✅ Accessibility enhancements\n✅ Semantic color and spacing variables\n\nThe CSS follows the exact class structure from the HTML, ensuring a perfect match. I've added:\n- Responsive layouts for features, pricing, and logos\n- Grayscale logo treatment\n- Card-based design for testimonials\n- Subtle button hover effects\n- Mobile breakpoint at 768px\n- Accessibility considerations like reduced motion and focus styles\n\nThe design maintains a professional, tech-forward aesthetic while providing clear visual hierarchy and interaction cues.\n\nWould you like me to make any specific adjustments to the design?\n\n### js_interactor\nI've written the `app.js` file with the requested interactive features for the FlowSync landing page. Let me break down the key aspects of the implementation:\n\n1. **Testimonial Carousel**:\n   - Uses `data-testimonial` attributes for targeting\n   - Supports next/prev buttons\n   - Handles cycling through testimonials\n   - Adds accessibility attributes (`aria-hidden`)\n   - Wraps in error-safe checks to prevent issues if elements are missing\n\n2. **Mobile Menu Toggle**:\n   - Targets `.nav-toggle` and `.nav-menu`\n   - Toggles visibility of menu\n   - Uses `aria-expanded` for accessibility\n   - Adds `.is-visible` class for styling\n\n3. **Smooth Scroll**:\n   - Targets all anchor links with `href=\"#...\"`\n   - Prevents default link behavior\n   - Uses `scrollIntoView()` with smooth behavior\n   - Safely handles missing target elements\n\n4. **Form Validation**:\n   - Targets form with `id='trial-form'`\n   - Validates email using regex\n   - Provides user feedback via alert\n   - Adds `aria-invalid` for accessibility\n   - Resets form after successful submission\n\nThe code follows modern ES6+ practices:\n- Uses `const`/`let` for variable declarations\n- Arrow function syntax\n- Event delegation\n- Modular function design\n- Defensive programming with existence checks\n\nAccessibility considerations:\n- ARIA attributes for screen readers\n- Focus management\n- Error state handling\n\nThe implementation assumes the HTML includes appropriate data attributes and classes, as specified in the requirements. It provides lightweight, non-blocking interactivity that enhances the user experience without overcomplicating the code.\n\n### integrator\nNow I'll merge the content and create the updated index.html::\n\n<:antml:function_\ncalls>\n><tml invoke name=\"write_file\">\">\n<an:parameter name path=\"index.\">.\">\n<:parameter name=\">content\nDOCTYPE><lang=\"\">\n\nhead>\n\">    <meta charset=\"=\"=\"-\">\n    >    meta name name=\"viewport\"\"\" content=\"=\"width device-width, width, initial--scale===1..0\n    meta name\"=\"description\"\"\" content=\"-=\"-powered project management platform for remote teams\">\">\n    <=\"title\">=\"\">owSync - AI Project Management for Remote Teams\">title>    \nrel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"=\"href styles.css\">\">\">\nhead>\n>\n\n<body>>\n    <header>>>        nav>\n\n            <-<1>Flow</h>\n            href=\"#features\">Features</</</a>\n>            a href=\"#Pricing\">\">\"></pricing a\n<a href=\"#=\"#=\"testimonials\">\">            testimon</a>>\n            href=\"#ccta\">\">\">Start Free Trial</a>>>        </> 